    • Constructor Detail

      • Table.Entry

        public Table.Entry(java.lang.String columnName,
           int dataType,
           T data,
           java.lang.reflect.Method setter)
            throws SQLInPUTException
        Constructs an Entry with the given data of the specified type in the designated column. This entry uses the given method to set parameters of PreparedStatement:s to the data of this entry.
        Parameters:
        columnName - The name of the column in which this entry is placed.
        dataType - The type of the data of this entry, which must be defined in the class Types.
        data - The data of this entry.
        setter - A method that can be used to set parameters of PreparedStatement:s to the data of this entry.
        Throws:
        SQLInPUTException - If the specified data type isn't one of the types defined in the class java.sql.Types, or if the given method isn't one of the PreparedStatement class' setter methods.

    • Method Detail

      • setPreparedStatementParameter

        public void setPreparedStatementParameter(java.sql.PreparedStatement ps,
                                 int index)
                                   throws SQLInPUTException
        Sets the designated parameter of the given PreparedStatement to the data of this entry.
        Parameters:
        ps - The PreparedStatement whose designated parameter shall be set to the data of this entry.
        index - The index of the parameter that shall be set to the data of this entry.
        Throws:
        SQLInPUTException - If the parameter cannot be set to the data of this entry.
